    <mainText>Leftist loon Chris Hayes, host of little-watched All In With Chris Hayes on MSNBC, took to Twitter to bless us with his idiocy on Monday, expressing his relief that the radical Islamic terrorist who attacked New York over the weekend used bombs rather than guns for the attack. We're also very very lucky that the attackers tried to use explosives rather than guns. — Christopher Hayes (@chrislhayes) September 19, 2016  God only knows how to interpret Hayes’ logic. I’m not even going to take a stab at it. However, the reaction on Twitter was immediate and brutal: @chrislhayes and knives rather than a gun in Minnesota — Sam Stein (@samsteinhp) September 19, 2016  Even actor Nick Searcy weighed in… Hey, by the way, how did that guy with the knife in MN get stopped? OMG IT WAS A GUN THAT STOPPED HIS KNIFE!!!! @samsteinhp @chrislhayes — Yes, Nick $earcy! (@yesnicksearcy) September 19, 2016  Because as we all know, bombs are preferred to “evil” guns, right Chris? @chrislhayes He shot a cop this morning. One person. His bomb injured 29, and could have been a lot more deadly. — Charles C. W. Cooke (@charlescwcooke) September 19, 2016  Some wise advice from the crowd: Buy guns. You have a duty to protect others. And it enrages liberals who want you helpless. Win-win.@Mark_Meed @chrislhayes — Kurt Schlichter (@KurtSchlichter) September 19, 2016  This expression explains it all: .@chrislhayes Uh. pic.twitter.com/M2X6uIeFrx — Tom Nichols (@RadioFreeTom) September 19, 2016  Bombs could hurt and/or kill people a lot faster than guns, Chris. Probably Hayes and his progressive leftist Democrat ilk, from Obama on down, would have loved for guns to be used rather than bombs because then they could use the attack as an anti-Second Amendment rights issue. But since a knife was used in Minnesota and bombs were used in New York, Hayes and lunatics like him won’t have that luxury. Oh, and Chris, there are already plenty of laws against stabbing people and setting off bombs. Why aren’t you asking for more knife or bomb control, hmmm?  Email Subscribe</mainText>
